ElementDescription: The NDAR Global Unique Identifier (GUID) for research subject
Subject ID how it's defined in lab/project
Age in months at the time of the interview/test/sampling/imaging.
Notes: Age is rounded to chronological month. If the research participant is 15-days-old at time of interview, the appropriate value would be 0 months. If the participant is 16-days-old, the value would be 1 month.

ElementDescription: Date on which the interview/genetic test/sampling/imaging/biospecimen was completed. MM/DD/YYYY
Sex of subject at birth
Notes: M = Male; F = Female; O=Other; NR = Not reported

ElementDescription: Name of task.
Description of experiment/sequence/event
Software used during experiment
Type of Stimulus Presented
Notes: 1 = more of 1st choice; 2=more of second choice

ElementDescription: Type of Response Presented
Notes: 1 = more of 1st choice; 2=more of second choice

ElementDescription: Confidence in choice
response time in ms for the decision
response time in ms for the confidence
Feedback Provided?
Notes: 0=no feedback was provided on this trial; 1=feedback was provided

ElementDescription: Number of Trials
Trial number
Trial Duration and Units ie 20 minutes
Data file 1
Visit name
Administration method:

Trial 1: 3 losing tokens, 3 winning tokens - response time in ms

Trial 2: 1 losing token, 5 winning tokens - response time in ms
